    {
      "name": "9. MCP Trigger Flow (Custom Tool)",
      "description": "End-to-end: create flow, configure MCP trigger, add Code + Reply, publish, call the hashed tool name.\n\nStep numbering: Step 1 only creates an empty flow (default trigger name is `trigger`). There is NO separate request named \"Step 1 update\" — Step 2 (`ap_update_trigger`) is what replaces/configures that trigger as the MCP Tool piece. After Step 3 adds the Code step, use Step 3b to map `personName` via API (MCP webhook does not auto-fill Code `inputs`; publish before calling the tool so the webhook runs the published version).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Step 1 - Create Flow",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 40,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"ap_create_flow\",\n        \"arguments\": { \"flowName\": \"Greeting MCP Tool\" }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Create the flow. Copy the flowId from the response into the collection variable."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 2 - Set MCP Trigger (updates trigger from Step 1)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 41,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"ap_update_trigger\",\n        \"arguments\": {\n            \"flowId\": \"{{flowId}}\",\n            \"pieceName\": \"@activepieces/piece-mcp\",\n            \"pieceVersion\": \"~0.0.17\",\n            \"triggerName\": \"mcp_tool\",\n            \"input\": {\n                \"toolName\": \"get_greeting\",\n                \"toolDescription\": \"Returns a greeting for the given name\",\n                \"inputSchema\": [\n                    {\n                        \"name\": \"personName\",\n                        \"type\": \"Text\",\n                        \"required\": true,\n                        \"description\": \"The name of the person to greet\"\n                    }\n                ],\n                \"returnsResponse\": true\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "This is the trigger configuration step after create — `ap_update_trigger` on the existing `trigger` step (internal name stays `trigger` on new flows). MCP tool name, params, and wait-for-response.\n\nFor inputSchema[].type use exact labels: Text, Boolean, Date, Number, Array, Object (not TEXT/NUMBER)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 3 - Add Code Step",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 42,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"ap_add_step\",\n        \"arguments\": {\n            \"flowId\": \"{{flowId}}\",\n            \"parentStepName\": \"trigger\",\n            \"stepLocationRelativeToParent\": \"AFTER\",\n            \"stepType\": \"CODE\",\n            \"displayName\": \"Build Greeting\"\n        }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Add a CODE skeleton (first action is usually `step_1`). Edit source in the UI: use `export const code`, not `run`.\n\nThen run Step 3b to map `personName`, or in the UI Inputs set personName = {{trigger.personName}} (internal trigger name is `trigger` unless renamed)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 3b - Map Code step input personName (ap_update_step)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 47,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"ap_update_step\",\n        \"arguments\": {\n            \"flowId\": \"{{flowId}}\",\n            \"stepName\": \"step_1\",\n            \"input\": {\n                \"personName\": \"{{trigger.personName}}\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Maps MCP tool arguments into the Code step: `inputs.personName` is resolved from the trigger output. Default new-flow trigger **internal** name is `trigger`; use `ap_flow_structure` if your code step is not `step_1` or names differ. This does not change Code **source** (still set `export const code` in the UI). Required for correct MCP `tools/call` unless you set the same mapping in the builder."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 4 - Add Reply Action",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 43,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"ap_add_step\",\n        \"arguments\": {\n            \"flowId\": \"{{flowId}}\",\n            \"parentStepName\": \"step_1\",\n            \"stepLocationRelativeToParent\": \"AFTER\",\n            \"stepType\": \"PIECE\",\n            \"displayName\": \"Reply to MCP Client\",\n            \"pieceName\": \"@activepieces/piece-mcp\",\n            \"pieceVersion\": \"~0.0.17\",\n            \"actionName\": \"reply_to_mcp_client\"\n        }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Add the Reply to MCP Client action."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 5 - Configure Reply",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 44,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"ap_update_step\",\n        \"arguments\": {\n            \"flowId\": \"{{flowId}}\",\n            \"stepName\": \"step_2\",\n            \"input\": {\n                \"mode\": \"simple\",\n                \"response\": {\n                    \"response\": {\n                        \"message\": \"{{step_1.greeting}}\"\n                    }\n                },\n                \"respond\": \"stop\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Configure Reply to MCP Client. In Simple mode the inner response must be an object (e.g. message key), not a bare string — otherwise the UI splits the string into one character per row. Use response.response.message or switch to Advanced + JSON."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 6 - Publish Flow",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 45,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"ap_lock_and_publish\",\n        \"arguments\": { \"flowId\": \"{{flowId}}\" }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Publish and enable the flow. After this, the tool appears in tools/list."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Step 7 - Call Custom Tool",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json, text/event-stream" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n    \"id\": 46,\n    \"method\": \"tools/call\",\n    \"params\": {\n        \"name\": \"REPLACE_WITH_NAME_FROM_tools_list\",\n        \"arguments\": {\n            \"personName\": \"Alice\"\n        }\n    }\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"]
            },
            "description": "Call the custom MCP tool. Flow tools are NOT named {toolName}_mcp. Server builds: sanitize(lowercase(toolName + '_' + flowId.slice(0,4))) + '_' + 6-char hash + '_mcp'. Example: get_greeting + rCIt... → get_greeting_rcit_nyht0e_mcp. Always run List All Tools first and copy the exact name. Flow must be ENABLED and published."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
